{
  "doc_id": "48291",
  "text": "Oleaginous microalgae, fungi and yeasts typically start accumulating storage lipids at N (or other nutrient) limitation and excess of C or energy [CITATION_1] Prochazkova et al. 2014) . In contrast, thraustochytrids are reported to accumulate storage lipids during either their growth period [CITATION_2] or when exposed to N and/or O 2 limitation [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] .",
